Introduction
Morse code, with its unique patterns, has played a significant role in communication history. In this tutorial, you'll dive into the world of Morse code and create a fully functional translator that converts Morse code into readable text and vice versa.

Prerequisites
To make the most of this project, basic knowledge of Python programming and coding concepts is recommended. Familiarity with string manipulation in Python will also be helpful.

Installation
To run the Morse code translator on your local machine, follow these steps:

Clone this repository to your computer: git clone https://github.com/your-username/morse-code-translator.git
Navigate to the project directory: cd morse-code-translator
Install any necessary dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
Usage
After installing the required dependencies, use the Morse code translator by executing the Python script with the following command:

Copy code
python morse_code.py
Follow the on-screen instructions to input Morse code and see the translated text.

Features
Effortlessly translate Morse code to text and vice versa.
Intuitive user interface for smooth interaction.
Robust and efficient Python codebase.
Gain insights into string manipulation techniques and Python fundamentals.
